WEBVTT

00:01.714 --> 00:03.985
(waves crashing)

00:11.165 --> 00:13.436
♪♪ ♪♪

00:25.628 --> 00:27.699
(moaning softly)

00:42.629 --> 00:44.733
-Ow!
-What?

00:44.800 --> 00:47.171
Something bit me.

00:47.238 --> 00:49.543
Am I bleeding?

00:52.281 --> 00:54.987
TOM:
Shit, you're right.

00:55.053 --> 00:58.260
Great. What the fuck was that?

01:04.873 --> 01:06.409
No, no, that can't be real.

01:06.476 --> 01:09.415
That's got to be left over
from Halloween or something.

01:26.550 --> 01:28.788
♪♪ ♪♪

01:57.679 --> 01:59.816
♪♪ ♪♪

02:24.298 --> 02:26.570
♪♪ ♪♪

02:35.722 --> 02:37.358
Dr. Wells.

02:38.694 --> 02:40.631
There are two gentlemen
here to see you.

02:42.702 --> 02:44.105
PATRICK:
You know, I really should be

02:44.171 --> 02:46.242
questioning her alone.

02:46.309 --> 02:49.415
Spare me the "I'm a cop
and you're not" lecture.

02:49.482 --> 02:52.121
Well, I'm more than just a cop,
Gino, I'm a detective.

02:52.187 --> 02:54.191
You're a detective,
I'm a reporter.

02:54.258 --> 02:55.595
We're both investigators, okay?

02:55.661 --> 02:57.297
-So, easy.
-(door opens)

02:57.364 --> 03:00.404
Hello, I'm Dr. Hannah Wells.
How may I help you?

03:00.470 --> 03:02.542
Hey, I'm Detective Read.
This is my friend Gino,

03:02.609 --> 03:05.648
-Gino Barelli. Downtown Native.
-from the, uh, Downtown Native.
That's...

03:05.715 --> 03:07.217
(clears throat)
We'd like to talk to you about

03:07.284 --> 03:08.554
the blood samples you took

03:08.621 --> 03:11.159
the night of The Ascension
bar firebombing.

03:12.094 --> 03:13.564
Look,

03:13.631 --> 03:15.568
we're not interested
in why you took those samples,

03:15.635 --> 03:17.739
okay, or whatever research
you're conducting here,

03:17.806 --> 03:19.576
but it's very possible
you took the blood

03:19.643 --> 03:21.045
of someone we're looking for.

03:21.112 --> 03:23.049
I'm afraid I can't
talk about that.

03:23.116 --> 03:25.287
-My research is confidential.
-You must've heard about

03:25.353 --> 03:27.559
the most recent murders
of gay men in this city.

03:27.625 --> 03:28.894
Of course.

03:28.961 --> 03:30.397
So, we feel that the killer

03:30.464 --> 03:31.934
was at St. Vincent's that night,

03:32.000 --> 03:33.537
and if you took his blood,
you might have his name

03:33.604 --> 03:35.006
-and information.
-I'm sorry,

03:35.073 --> 03:36.844
I wish I could help you.

03:36.910 --> 03:38.848
Why don't you just

03:38.914 --> 03:40.885
take a moment to look
through your records.

03:40.952 --> 03:42.889
I'm sure it
won't take that long.

03:42.956 --> 03:44.526
My time isn't the issue.

03:44.593 --> 03:46.028
I'd be betraying
patient confidentiality.

03:46.095 --> 03:47.398
PATRICK:
Yeah, I understand.

03:48.199 --> 03:50.772
Nobody needs to know
what we're talking about here.

03:50.838 --> 03:53.544
Okay?
And given the stakes,

03:53.611 --> 03:55.982
it's very likely
you could be saving lives.

03:56.048 --> 03:58.253
And you wouldn't be aiding
and abetting a murderer.

03:58.319 --> 03:59.790
We're done here.

03:59.856 --> 04:03.296
GINO:
This man preys
on the gay community.

04:03.363 --> 04:06.135
He butchers them.
He cuts them up.

04:06.202 --> 04:07.672
He slices off their heads,

04:07.739 --> 04:09.976
-their hands...
-HANNAH: This isn't an official

04:10.043 --> 04:11.680
investigation, is it?

04:11.747 --> 04:13.450
-What are you talking about?
-Detectives usually

04:13.517 --> 04:15.888
don't travel around
with reporters.

04:17.592 --> 04:19.228
The police in this city

04:19.295 --> 04:21.500
don't give a shit
about dead gay men,

04:21.567 --> 04:24.405
so we're looking into this
as private citizens.

04:26.409 --> 04:27.679
This is the man

04:27.745 --> 04:31.018
we're looking for.
Do you recognize him?

04:34.024 --> 04:35.495
That mark-- have you
had it checked out?

04:35.561 --> 04:37.197
I've seen similar discolorations

04:37.264 --> 04:38.934
in several of my patients.

04:39.001 --> 04:40.403
-Let me see.
-Gino.

04:40.470 --> 04:41.773
It's just... It's a bug bite.

04:41.840 --> 04:43.511
HANNAH:
If you two are partners,

04:43.577 --> 04:45.313
you both might want
to get checked out.

04:45.380 --> 04:47.251
I've only been seeing it
in gay men.

04:47.317 --> 04:50.423
Uh, all right, can we just
stick to the subject here?

04:50.491 --> 04:51.794
There's a killer at large.

04:51.860 --> 04:53.931
I've made myself clear.
No one cares more

04:53.998 --> 04:55.835
about the well-being
of your community than I do,

04:55.902 --> 04:58.239
and if you go about the proper
channels to obtain a warrant,

04:58.306 --> 04:59.676
I'd be happy to comply.

04:59.743 --> 05:01.580
In the meantime,

05:01.647 --> 05:04.986
consider making an appointment
for a checkup.

05:22.421 --> 05:23.624
Hey.

05:23.691 --> 05:25.026
-Yeah?
-MULCAHEY: I just got a call

05:25.093 --> 05:26.429
from the administrator

05:26.497 --> 05:27.765
over at St. Vincent's.
Said you were down there

05:27.832 --> 05:29.603
flashing a sketch
of the Mai Tai Killer.

05:29.669 --> 05:32.074
Yeah, just following up
on some questions I still have.

05:32.140 --> 05:34.646
Well, we told them that we were
done with all the interviews.

05:34.713 --> 05:36.015
They're starting to worry
if we think

05:36.082 --> 05:37.852
the killer might be
one of their staff.

05:37.919 --> 05:39.890
Then they're idiots 'cause
I didn't imply that at all.

05:39.956 --> 05:42.027
I don't have to explain
my moves to you, Mulcahey.

05:42.094 --> 05:43.497
Go back to your desk,

05:43.564 --> 05:46.603
carry on making ignorant
gay cracks behind my back, okay?

05:46.670 --> 05:48.674
-(sniffs)
-You know what?

05:48.741 --> 05:50.678
For somebody who always seems
to have the answers,

05:50.745 --> 05:52.916
you don't know jack shit.

05:54.886 --> 05:56.924
(phone rings)

06:02.034 --> 06:03.804
Detective Read.

06:03.871 --> 06:06.442
Detective, my name
is Frankie Del Rios.

06:06.510 --> 06:09.181
I live out on Fire Island.

06:09.248 --> 06:10.685
Okay.
What can I do for you?

06:10.751 --> 06:12.154
I was gonna call
the regular island police,

06:12.221 --> 06:13.958
but we heard
from a friend of a friend

06:14.024 --> 06:16.930
that you're different.
That you're one of us.

06:16.997 --> 06:18.767
Anyways, my friend and I,

06:18.834 --> 06:20.905
we found something
on the beach, Detective.

06:20.972 --> 06:22.842
It's a body.
It's been there for a while.

06:22.909 --> 06:26.249
Oh, and this guy is wearing
a black leather mask.

06:26.315 --> 06:27.885
-A leather mask?
-Yeah.

06:27.952 --> 06:29.623
It's on the north shore,
behind the house

06:29.689 --> 06:32.461
at 4 Seafront Drive.

06:35.233 --> 06:36.503
Have you told anyone about this?

06:36.570 --> 06:39.008
You're the first person
I called.

06:39.074 --> 06:40.310
Okay, good.

06:40.377 --> 06:41.647
Listen to me very carefully.

06:41.713 --> 06:43.617
Keep this to yourself,
understood?

06:44.953 --> 06:48.126
Easy, easy, easy. It's
a sculpture you're uncrating,

06:48.192 --> 06:50.831
not a Frigidaire.

06:50.898 --> 06:52.535
You know, you two
should thank me.

06:52.602 --> 06:54.405
Your tiny, little worldviews
are about to expand

06:54.471 --> 06:56.442
just by looking at it.

07:00.083 --> 07:02.187
(phone rings)

07:05.226 --> 07:07.832
Gently, gently.

07:12.007 --> 07:12.875
Hello?

07:12.942 --> 07:14.746
Hello, Sam.
It's Patrick.

07:14.813 --> 07:16.950
We have a problem.

07:17.017 --> 07:18.286
Oh, wonderful.
Just when I thought

07:18.353 --> 07:19.756
I was running short on those.

07:19.823 --> 07:22.562
No, I'm serious.
Two guys found a body.

07:23.329 --> 07:24.966
On Fire Island.

07:35.286 --> 07:37.792
So, what are we doing out here?

07:37.859 --> 07:39.529
Why aren't we meeting
at the club?

07:39.596 --> 07:40.865
Front page.

07:42.535 --> 07:43.937
Fifth article this month
by this guy,

07:44.004 --> 07:47.645
shitting on the police.
He's stirring things up.

07:47.712 --> 07:49.916
And it's not just the fruits,

07:49.983 --> 07:52.087
regular people
are starting to talk.

07:52.154 --> 07:53.824
No offense.

07:54.592 --> 07:56.062
So, what do we care?

07:56.128 --> 07:57.130
We're not the police.

07:57.197 --> 07:59.669
But some of the police
are with us.

07:59.736 --> 08:01.172
Look, we need them to get
certain things done,

08:01.238 --> 08:03.042
you understand?
They're our friends.

08:03.109 --> 08:06.449
-You know how this works.
-Sure, Angelo.

08:06.516 --> 08:08.587
And now some of our friends

08:08.654 --> 08:10.691
have asked us to take care
of this problem.

08:10.758 --> 08:12.060
Quiet things down.

08:12.127 --> 08:13.831
Is that really necessary?

08:13.897 --> 08:15.400
(laughs)

08:15.467 --> 08:17.572
When the boss
says it's necessary,

08:17.638 --> 08:19.776
then it's fucking necessary.

08:19.843 --> 08:23.751
-Right.
-This falls on you.

08:23.817 --> 08:26.088
Look, we don't care how
you do it, but no showboating.

08:26.155 --> 08:29.028
We don't want anything found.
Just, uh...

08:29.094 --> 08:30.731
disappear this guy,

08:30.798 --> 08:33.904
make sure he's written
his last fucking article.

08:42.555 --> 08:45.661
Oh, Gino.

08:57.652 --> 08:59.956
-Where are you going?
-They found a body.

09:00.023 --> 09:03.296
Think it might be related
to the Mai Tai Killer

09:03.362 --> 09:04.766
on Fire Island.

09:04.833 --> 09:07.237
Fire Island? Why did...
Why are they calling you?

09:07.304 --> 09:08.640
Apparently, I'm the only cop

09:08.707 --> 09:10.678
gay enough to care.

09:10.745 --> 09:12.582
-Okay, well, I'll come with you.
-No.

09:12.648 --> 09:14.118
-No.
-No?

09:14.184 --> 09:16.222
No. I-I don't want to make
a whole scene of this.

09:16.288 --> 09:17.457
It's not my jurisdiction.

09:17.525 --> 09:19.496
I got to tread lightly.

09:19.562 --> 09:22.502
I'm... confused.
This is...

09:22.568 --> 09:24.471
So, you're gonna
spend the night?

09:24.539 --> 09:27.010
Uh... I don't know.

09:27.077 --> 09:28.947
Hopefully not.

09:29.014 --> 09:30.250
I'll call.

09:30.316 --> 09:31.853
(kisses)

09:32.588 --> 09:34.859
Are you fucking someone?

09:37.865 --> 09:40.203
My life is complicated enough
right now

09:40.270 --> 09:42.575
without a jealous partner.

09:42.642 --> 09:45.614
Please don't
be that person, Gino.

09:48.520 --> 09:50.825
(door closes)

10:19.348 --> 10:21.152
♪♪ ♪♪

10:39.556 --> 10:41.860
(door closes)

10:47.839 --> 10:50.143
-Hello, Gino.
-Jesus!

10:50.210 --> 10:51.913
(sighs)

10:51.980 --> 10:53.951
How'd you get in here?

10:54.017 --> 10:56.756
Well, you left the door open
when you ran down the stairs.

10:57.758 --> 10:59.629
You know,
you're better than this, Gino.

10:59.696 --> 11:02.100
Young men are a waste of time.

11:02.167 --> 11:04.806
Oh, sure, they're fun
in bed, but...

11:05.774 --> 11:07.077
...it never lasts.

11:07.143 --> 11:09.281
What the fuck are you doing
in my apartment?

11:12.320 --> 11:13.322
(clears throat)

11:13.389 --> 11:14.759
You know,

11:14.826 --> 11:17.264
the men who run this town--

11:17.330 --> 11:20.504
not the politicians, but
the ones with the real power--

11:20.571 --> 11:22.440
they need people like me

11:22.508 --> 11:25.313
to be their eyes and their ears,

11:25.380 --> 11:26.750
watch the books,

11:26.816 --> 11:28.887
that sort of thing.

11:28.954 --> 11:31.392
You know, or worse.

11:31.458 --> 11:34.164
I'm not just a barfly.

11:34.231 --> 11:36.803
-You're a fucking hit man?
-That term

11:36.870 --> 11:38.840
is gauche.

11:40.476 --> 11:41.880
These men are unhappy

11:41.947 --> 11:43.750
with what you've
been writing in the Native.

11:43.817 --> 11:45.554
It's bringing
the wrong kind of attention

11:45.621 --> 11:48.527
to their establishments,
it's affecting the bottom line.

11:48.594 --> 11:51.065
It has to stop.

11:51.131 --> 11:52.568
Or else...

11:52.635 --> 11:54.404
I'm gonna have to do something

11:54.471 --> 11:55.941
I really don't want to do

11:56.008 --> 11:59.081
to that pretty little face
of yours.

12:00.751 --> 12:02.755
Who are you really
working for, Henry?

12:03.557 --> 12:05.059
You get rid of me...

12:05.828 --> 12:07.430
...you're only
helping the killer.

12:07.498 --> 12:09.769
Ugh!
This obsession

12:09.836 --> 12:12.440
is unhealthy, Gino.
Get rid of it.

12:12.508 --> 12:15.113
He's already moved on to Fire
Island. They found a new body.

12:15.179 --> 12:16.382
Fire Island?

12:36.355 --> 12:38.359
Are you Patrick?

12:39.796 --> 12:41.800
Is he a cop, too?

12:41.866 --> 12:44.371
-I'm Tom, this is Freddy.
-Frankie.

12:44.438 --> 12:46.008
-(snorts)
-TOM: Right.

12:46.075 --> 12:47.377
Can we see your badge, please?

12:47.444 --> 12:49.247
Sorry, I just figure
there's probably

12:49.314 --> 12:51.318
some kind of criminal exposure
for finding a body

12:51.385 --> 12:52.888
and not reporting it
to the cops.

12:52.955 --> 12:54.458
And the finger cut me.

12:54.525 --> 12:56.596
Do you think I could get
some sort of disease from that?

12:56.663 --> 12:59.334
No.
I wouldn't worry about it.

13:00.571 --> 13:02.875
Come on, we'll show you
where the body is.

13:02.942 --> 13:04.879
We're cops.
We can find it.

13:04.946 --> 13:06.482
You can go.

13:07.852 --> 13:10.924
-Uh...
-Leave.

13:10.991 --> 13:13.095
This is a crime scene now.

13:13.162 --> 13:14.364
And if either of you fuckers

13:14.431 --> 13:15.901
-tell anybody about...
-All right.

13:15.968 --> 13:17.972
Thank you for your services,
gentlemen.

13:18.039 --> 13:19.241
For your own security,

13:19.308 --> 13:22.080
we need to keep this
between us, okay?

13:23.382 --> 13:25.554
Okay.

13:42.487 --> 13:44.525
♪♪ ♪♪

14:01.458 --> 14:04.866
God, I miss it here.

14:09.174 --> 14:11.211
I think this is
the only place I ever felt

14:11.278 --> 14:13.617
-truly relaxed.
-That's probably a result

14:13.683 --> 14:16.088
of the drugs, Sam.

14:17.591 --> 14:19.061
What were we thinking,
burying him

14:19.127 --> 14:20.764
in a shallow sand dune, Patrick?

14:20.831 --> 14:22.501
Yet again...

14:23.870 --> 14:26.008
...probably the drugs.

14:52.695 --> 14:55.433
So, what do we do?

14:55.501 --> 14:57.505
We dig more.

14:57.571 --> 14:59.274
The remains we scattered
ought to be around here.

14:59.341 --> 15:01.111
We need to get those remains
in our bag

15:01.178 --> 15:02.615
and bury them somewhere safe.

15:02.681 --> 15:04.184
Safe?
Wh-What is safe

15:04.251 --> 15:05.921
-for a rotting twink, Patrick?
-You know what, Sam,

15:05.988 --> 15:07.992
I haven't really thought
about that yet, okay?

15:08.058 --> 15:09.796
Just get digging.
This poor kid

15:09.862 --> 15:11.064
deserved way more than this.

15:11.131 --> 15:13.570
GINO:
But you killed him anyway.

15:13.637 --> 15:15.707
Henry, wh...
Who the fuck is this?

15:15.774 --> 15:17.477
Hello, Sam.
I brought him.

15:17.545 --> 15:19.381
He wanted to know
about the killer.

15:19.448 --> 15:22.688
I just left out the part that
the killer was his boyfriend.

15:24.257 --> 15:25.828
The fuck is going on
here, Patrick?

15:25.894 --> 15:27.230
It's not what you think, Gino.

15:27.297 --> 15:28.633
-All right, tell him.
-PATRICK: Go home, Gino.

15:28.700 --> 15:30.804
I'll talk about this
when I get back. This has

15:30.871 --> 15:33.543
nothing to do with you.
You are not a part of this.

15:35.079 --> 15:37.885
But the three of you are?

15:37.952 --> 15:40.389
What is this,
some sort of murder cult?

15:40.456 --> 15:42.293
-(Patrick scoffs)
-Did you kill Barbara?

15:42.360 --> 15:44.164
No, we did not fucking kill
Barbara. I didn't kill anybody.

15:44.231 --> 15:46.636
This was a mistake, okay?
This was a freak accident,

15:46.703 --> 15:48.305
a horrible thing
that shouldn't have happened.

15:48.372 --> 15:50.711
But you're gonna
want to hear all about it.

15:50.777 --> 15:52.313
It's quite the heck of a story.

15:52.380 --> 15:53.850
Although I'm not sure
it's gonna end up

15:53.917 --> 15:56.255
in the pages of The Native.

16:02.768 --> 16:04.672
This is Sam's house.

16:04.739 --> 16:06.341
Okay?

16:07.310 --> 16:09.849
I met Sam the first time
I ever came to Fire Island.

16:09.916 --> 16:12.187
("Beat of the Night"
by Fever playing)

16:26.348 --> 16:28.753
SAM:
Party's this way.

16:28.820 --> 16:30.524
Coming?

16:30.591 --> 16:32.995
PATRICK:
Sam scooped me up,

16:33.062 --> 16:35.366
fresh off the ferry,

16:35.433 --> 16:37.872
and that's when I met Billy.

16:37.938 --> 16:41.011
Billy was his name.

16:44.351 --> 16:46.523
I was married to Barbara,
but I lied to her.

16:46.589 --> 16:48.793
I told her I was working
on a stakeout,

16:48.860 --> 16:52.535
but I went to the island
so I could be myself.

17:01.519 --> 17:05.393
Billy was fresh off the bus.
I can't remember where from,

17:05.459 --> 17:08.132
but one of those places
that kept him bottled up.

17:08.934 --> 17:12.407
♪♪ The night is on, dancing
to the brightness, the lights♪♪

17:12.473 --> 17:16.014
♪♪ Ooh, disco lights ♪♪

17:16.081 --> 17:17.518
♪♪ We know you're too hot ♪♪

17:17.585 --> 17:20.991
♪♪ To stay here at all ♪♪

17:21.058 --> 17:23.095
♪♪ You know you're too hot ♪♪

17:23.162 --> 17:24.264
♪♪ The night is still young... ♪♪

17:24.331 --> 17:26.903
He was this firecracker

17:26.970 --> 17:29.341
of energy and joy.

17:29.407 --> 17:31.345
I was from New York,

17:31.411 --> 17:33.315
but that night
I might as well have been

17:33.382 --> 17:35.219
from Akron or Tulsa

17:35.286 --> 17:37.190
or wherever Billy was from.

17:37.257 --> 17:40.429
I was letting myself go.

17:46.108 --> 17:48.513
Sam gave us coke.

17:48.580 --> 17:51.151
It was the first time
for both of us.

17:51.218 --> 17:52.888
♪♪ As you dance to the beat ♪♪

17:52.955 --> 17:55.393
♪♪ Ooh, as you dance
to the beat... ♪♪

17:55.459 --> 17:58.500
SAM:
(chuckles) But they loved it.

17:58.566 --> 18:01.004
My parties were the place to be.

18:01.071 --> 18:03.342
No fatties, no femmes.

18:03.409 --> 18:05.413
It was gay Woodstock
every weekend.

18:05.479 --> 18:10.824
♪♪ You mingle around ♪♪

18:10.891 --> 18:14.932
♪♪ You're just with someone
that wants to get down ♪♪

18:14.999 --> 18:16.769
♪♪ Get down, get down ♪♪

18:16.836 --> 18:18.773
-♪♪ Come on, dancing ♪♪
-♪♪ Dancing ♪♪

18:18.840 --> 18:20.677
-♪♪ Come on, dancing ♪♪
-♪♪ Ooh, dancing ♪♪

18:20.744 --> 18:22.581
-♪♪ Come on, dancing ♪♪
-♪♪ Dancing ♪♪

18:22.648 --> 18:25.721
♪♪ Come on, dancing
to the beat of the night ♪♪

18:25.787 --> 18:27.858
-♪♪ Come on, dancing ♪♪
-♪♪ Dancing ♪♪

18:27.925 --> 18:29.729
-♪♪ Come on,
dancing ♪♪
-♪♪ Dancing ♪♪

