18:34.538 --> 18:38.345
♪♪ To the beat
of the night ♪♪

18:38.412 --> 18:41.118
♪♪ Oh, come on, dancing ♪♪

18:41.184 --> 18:44.457
♪♪ Oh, to the beat of the night ♪♪

18:44.525 --> 18:46.763
(music continuing in distance)

18:53.375 --> 18:55.614
-♪♪ ♪♪
-(door closes)

19:03.329 --> 19:05.567
(pants unzip)

19:08.673 --> 19:10.577
Now what?

19:12.815 --> 19:16.088
Now we need someone
to volunteer.

19:16.154 --> 19:18.225
For what?

19:20.429 --> 19:22.668
To be the special one.

19:35.059 --> 19:36.596
I'll do it.

20:05.052 --> 20:08.225
(muffled grunt, chuckle)

20:30.035 --> 20:32.306
♪♪ ♪♪

20:57.089 --> 20:58.893
♪♪ ♪♪

21:17.764 --> 21:20.537
Let's make him feel special.

21:21.739 --> 21:23.308
(grunting)

21:25.112 --> 21:27.818
-You like that, don't you?
Yeah, you do.
-Mm-hmm.

21:30.690 --> 21:32.828
He's gonna like that, too.

21:34.430 --> 21:37.403
(Billy panting)

22:04.925 --> 22:05.827
Patrick.

22:05.894 --> 22:07.631
(grunting)

22:07.698 --> 22:09.067
SAM:
Patrick, stop.

22:10.035 --> 22:11.037
Hey.

22:11.104 --> 22:13.008
Patrick, stop it!

22:13.075 --> 22:15.446
-Hey, stop. Stop.
-What?

22:17.985 --> 22:20.122
(Patrick mumbles)

22:20.189 --> 22:22.426
(grunts)

22:27.738 --> 22:30.042
Hey. Hey.

22:31.077 --> 22:32.714
Hey.

22:37.758 --> 22:39.093
PATRICK:
Oh, my God. No, no, no.

22:39.160 --> 22:41.499
-No, no, no, no, no. Oh, shit.
-Oh, my God.

22:41.566 --> 22:43.402
-(Patrick grunting)
-Stop.

22:43.468 --> 22:44.972
-Patrick, stop.
-Come on, come on.

22:45.039 --> 22:48.011
-Stop it, Patrick.
-Come on, come on!

22:48.078 --> 22:50.517
-(grunting)
-Stop it!

22:50.584 --> 22:53.255
PATRICK:
Oh, fuck. Oh, come on, come on.

22:53.322 --> 22:54.658
Enough!

22:54.725 --> 22:56.729
Why the fuck are you
pulling a gun on me?!

22:56.796 --> 22:58.465
So you would stop
giving CPR to a dead kid.

22:58.533 --> 23:00.904
-PATRICK: Oh, my God, we
have to call the police.
-Fuck the cops.

23:00.971 --> 23:02.941
I am a cop!

23:03.008 --> 23:05.680
-Oh, shit.
-You're a fucking cop?

23:07.250 --> 23:09.053
You're a fucking cop?!

23:09.120 --> 23:11.559
-Why the fuck
didn't you tell me that?
-We can't go to the police.

23:11.626 --> 23:13.328
Why the fuck
didn't you tell me that?!

23:13.395 --> 23:16.334
My body's full
of fucking drugs. I...

23:16.401 --> 23:18.606
This poor kid,
this poor fucking kid.

23:18.673 --> 23:20.944
What have we done
to this poor kid?

23:21.946 --> 23:23.081
Oh, my God.

23:23.148 --> 23:24.752
I don't know.
It was an accident. He-he...

23:24.818 --> 23:27.089
he volunteered for it.
He consented.

23:27.156 --> 23:28.927
-It was...
-No. No.

23:28.993 --> 23:30.429
Not to this.

23:32.300 --> 23:34.070
Okay.

23:36.374 --> 23:38.145
I know someone who can help us.

23:38.211 --> 23:40.583
He's a, um, um...

23:40.650 --> 23:43.488
a fixer for the mob,
but he's, uh, one of us.

23:43.556 --> 23:46.829
He's-he's called
the Velvet Touch.

23:49.033 --> 23:50.369
I'm gonna call him.

23:50.436 --> 23:51.973
(picks up receiver)

23:52.039 --> 23:54.110
(dialing)

23:59.588 --> 24:00.857
(knock on door)

24:03.428 --> 24:05.834
Henry, thank God.

24:09.173 --> 24:10.710
HENRY:
Mm.

24:14.183 --> 24:15.620
Oh...

24:18.091 --> 24:20.630
Well, he's not very big.

24:20.697 --> 24:22.668
Thank God you're into twinks
and not bears.

24:22.734 --> 24:24.838
Enough with the jokes, Henry.
I need your help.

24:24.905 --> 24:26.542
Of course.

24:26.609 --> 24:28.078
It'll cost you ten grand.

24:28.145 --> 24:30.583
That's fine.

24:31.652 --> 24:34.390
This is my associate.

24:34.457 --> 24:37.497
He's a whiz
at cutting up bodies.

24:48.452 --> 24:50.557
-Is he one of us?
-HENRY: He's meat

24:50.623 --> 24:52.259
for butchering,
just like the others.

24:52.326 --> 24:55.567
They were criminals.
This is an innocent boy.

24:57.069 --> 24:59.374
Get to work,

24:59.440 --> 25:01.612
or else I'll have to call
your mother

25:01.679 --> 25:04.250
and tell her
about your sexuality.

25:05.119 --> 25:09.060
You don't want to break
her heart, do you?

25:11.131 --> 25:13.603
I can't watch this.

25:42.961 --> 25:45.800
♪♪ ♪♪

26:12.420 --> 26:14.725
♪♪ ♪♪

26:32.059 --> 26:34.097
(sawing)

26:39.808 --> 26:41.745
(grunts softly)

27:02.621 --> 27:04.791
♪♪ ♪♪

27:27.504 --> 27:29.808
♪♪ ♪♪

27:48.411 --> 27:49.748
What's your problem?

27:49.815 --> 27:51.685
(short exhale)

27:51.752 --> 27:54.525
He's so...

27:54.591 --> 27:56.695
beautiful.

27:59.701 --> 28:01.404
He deserved better.

28:01.471 --> 28:04.678
Someone should have been
watching out for him.

28:07.584 --> 28:09.855
Okay...

28:14.965 --> 28:18.238
GINO:
So, is that what you've been
hiding? That's the secret?

28:18.305 --> 28:20.242
-What happened that night?
-PATRICK: Please, just go home.

28:20.309 --> 28:23.649
-Gino, please, you deserve
way more than this.
-This is...

28:23.716 --> 28:25.319
SAM:
Look, I am really sorry

28:25.385 --> 28:27.189
that I forgot my violin
for this perfect little moment,

28:27.256 --> 28:28.926
but we do have a body
to dispose of,

28:28.993 --> 28:30.697
so you want to pitch in
or get the fuck out of here?

28:30.763 --> 28:32.701
No, he's not pitching in, okay?

28:32.767 --> 28:34.337
-Listen to me.
-HENRY: Well, he's either
an accomplice

28:34.403 --> 28:37.142
to the crime or he's
gonna be a whistleblower

28:37.209 --> 28:38.980
to his fag rag.
Isn't that right, Gino?

28:39.046 --> 28:43.021
I can't imagine you taking
a back seat for anyone.

28:47.096 --> 28:50.703
God, please, Gino.
What are you doing?

28:50.770 --> 28:53.441
Please, why are you helping?
Just stop.

28:53.509 --> 28:55.145
What are my options, Patrick?

28:55.914 --> 28:58.753
I can't call the cops

28:58.819 --> 29:01.224
because of you.

29:01.291 --> 29:02.894
I'm stuck.

29:05.700 --> 29:08.371
Well, at least now we can
give the kid a proper burial,

29:08.438 --> 29:10.342
rustle up a Casa Blanca lily
or two.

29:10.409 --> 29:12.681
Maybe we can contact
his family so they can

29:12.747 --> 29:14.985
-have some closure.
-HENRY: We're not
contacting anybody.

29:15.052 --> 29:17.389
This is going to remain
a John Doe.

29:18.759 --> 29:22.166
Hang on, these bones,
these bones.

29:22.232 --> 29:24.170
There's no cuts.

29:24.905 --> 29:26.609
Whoever did this

29:26.675 --> 29:28.779
dissected the body perfectly.

29:28.846 --> 29:31.050
Huh.
I'm not gonna hire a cleaner

29:31.117 --> 29:32.554
who doesn't know
what he's doing.

29:33.488 --> 29:36.695
What was his name?
Who did you bring that night?

29:36.762 --> 29:39.200
Nothing happened that night,
Patrick. You weren't here.

29:39.266 --> 29:41.872
I wasn't here.
None of us are here right now.

29:41.939 --> 29:43.509
You know, the Mai Tai Killer

29:43.576 --> 29:45.713
cuts up his victims
in exactly the same way

29:45.780 --> 29:48.819
-(scoffs)
-that the guy who has
dissected this body has.

29:48.886 --> 29:50.757
I have spent many years

29:50.823 --> 29:54.196
in my career, and I have never
seen cuts like this before,

29:54.263 --> 29:56.067
until these bodies
started arriving.

29:56.134 --> 29:59.240
Well, bravo, Mr. Policeman.
Why are we going down this road?

29:59.307 --> 30:01.879
We can't be throwing around
accusations like this,

30:01.945 --> 30:03.949
especially when we're
dealing with the mob.

30:04.016 --> 30:06.354
-What's his name, Henry?
-Well...

30:07.156 --> 30:09.661
...his name is Mr. Whitely.

30:09.728 --> 30:11.130
He's a male nurse,

30:11.197 --> 30:13.134
-and that's all I know.
-You know where he lives?

30:13.201 --> 30:14.504
Well, I could call him up
and ask him.

30:14.571 --> 30:17.042
I mean, maybe he'll ask us
over for tea.

30:17.109 --> 30:20.583
You have no proof
that this is your guy.

30:20.650 --> 30:22.419
I've seen his face.

30:22.486 --> 30:24.591
I can ID him.

30:24.658 --> 30:25.827
You take me to him.

30:25.893 --> 30:27.062
What are you
talking about, Gino?

30:27.129 --> 30:29.200
He would recognize you
right away.

30:29.266 --> 30:31.905
(sighs) Well, it's amazing
that Scooby-Doo here

30:31.972 --> 30:33.308
has solved the crime,
but before we all

30:33.375 --> 30:35.178
pile into the Mystery Machine,
can we please

30:35.245 --> 30:38.485
deal with the issue at hand?

30:39.253 --> 30:41.692
-Henry and I will go on our own.
-Oh, fuck that. Fuck...

30:41.759 --> 30:43.228
Gino, please.

30:43.294 --> 30:44.798
If I had an ounce of integrity,

30:44.865 --> 30:46.668
I'd turn your fucking ass in.

30:46.735 --> 30:49.106
Gino, wait. Wait.

30:52.580 --> 30:53.582
Take this.

30:53.649 --> 30:56.020
Please.

31:18.666 --> 31:21.037
ng)
-(scoffs)

31:23.743 --> 31:26.782
(phone rings)

31:26.849 --> 31:28.318
WHITELY:
If you've reached this,

31:28.384 --> 31:30.790
I am either unavailable
or at my office.

31:30.857 --> 31:32.594
-Please leave a message.
-(beep)

31:38.806 --> 31:41.444
(phone ringing)

31:45.419 --> 31:46.287
Hello?

31:46.354 --> 31:49.093
Mr. Whitely.
It's Henry.

31:49.160 --> 31:50.963
I've got another job for us.

31:51.030 --> 31:53.268
Henry.
This really isn't

31:53.334 --> 31:55.005
-the best time for me.
-(scoffs)

31:55.071 --> 31:57.710
Well, is it ever a good time
when I call?

31:57.777 --> 31:59.581
The boss has a mess

31:59.648 --> 32:02.252
-he needs us to clean up ASAP.
-I'm sorry,

32:02.319 --> 32:04.356
but I just can't do that
right now, unfortunately.

32:04.423 --> 32:05.993
Well, you know
we really don't have a choice

32:06.060 --> 32:07.530
in these matters, Whitely.

32:11.070 --> 32:13.475
Okay.
Where's the location?

32:13.542 --> 32:15.145
Um...

32:15.212 --> 32:18.619
I'm afraid I can't
give that to you.

32:18.686 --> 32:19.988
I'll pick you up.

32:20.055 --> 32:22.159
I'll just need an address.

32:22.226 --> 32:23.929
An address?

32:23.996 --> 32:25.232
I'm going to be out and about.

32:25.298 --> 32:28.772
How about we meet
at Malty's bar, 9:00 p. m.

32:28.839 --> 32:30.075
Sure.

32:30.142 --> 32:32.179
-See you soon.
-(hangs up)

32:37.322 --> 32:38.793
He knows something's up.

32:38.859 --> 32:40.028
What are you talking about?

32:40.095 --> 32:42.734
Change of plans.

32:42.801 --> 32:43.836
You're gonna ID him.

32:43.903 --> 32:45.740
If he's the Mai Tai killer,

32:45.807 --> 32:47.476
we take him out, then and there.

32:47.544 --> 32:48.478
(scoffs)

32:48.546 --> 32:51.184
Absolutely not, Henry.
No.

32:51.250 --> 32:53.454
I'll lure him
from the bar into the car,

32:53.522 --> 32:55.258
where you'll be waiting
in the back seat with a gun.

32:55.325 --> 32:56.829
-I'm not killing anyone.
-No,

32:56.895 --> 32:59.066
you just hold him at gunpoint.
We'll drive to the docks

32:59.133 --> 33:01.103
and I'll finish him off.

33:03.709 --> 33:06.280
You want to stop these killings,
isn't that right?

33:06.347 --> 33:08.251
Well, moral clarity's
a whole lot easier

33:08.318 --> 33:09.721
when you're sitting
behind a typewriter.

33:09.788 --> 33:11.959
We're doing this, Gino,

33:12.025 --> 33:14.263
and we're going it tonight.

33:16.635 --> 33:18.104
(engine starts)

33:18.873 --> 33:20.543
(thud)

33:28.291 --> 33:30.095
HENRY:
Well, that's his Buick.

33:30.161 --> 33:32.700
That's good.
Looks like he's inside already.

33:32.767 --> 33:35.171
GINO:
You do realize that this
is fucking insane, right?

33:35.238 --> 33:36.407
HENRY:
Gino,

33:36.474 --> 33:38.211
you just duck down
in the back seat,

33:38.278 --> 33:40.850
make sure nobody sees you,

33:40.917 --> 33:42.987
keep your finger on the trigger,

33:43.054 --> 33:46.762
and I will be back in five.

33:56.748 --> 33:59.019
(entry bells jingle)

34:01.057 --> 34:03.328
(door closes)

34:05.600 --> 34:07.604
Mr. Whitely.

34:07.670 --> 34:08.606
Henry.

34:08.672 --> 34:11.578
-Thank you for meeting here.
-Mm.

34:11.645 --> 34:14.818
I thought we could catch up
over a drink before we head out.

34:19.193 --> 34:21.732
I'll have a whiskey.

34:35.292 --> 34:36.662
-So, what's the job?
-Oh,

34:36.728 --> 34:39.734
couple of deadbeats
didn't pay their loan.

34:39.801 --> 34:43.709
Demarco is whacking people
over bad loans now?

34:43.776 --> 34:45.913
What happened to a lean?

34:45.980 --> 34:48.117
Maybe it's a big loan.

34:48.184 --> 34:50.790
It's none of my business,
nor yours.

34:58.939 --> 35:01.243
We should get going.

35:03.114 --> 35:04.985
Mind if I use the john first?

35:05.051 --> 35:07.790
You've never
needed my permission.

35:16.273 --> 35:20.415
(bathroom door opens, closes)

35:24.123 --> 35:26.394
♪♪ ♪♪

35:51.210 --> 35:53.281
Fuck.

36:14.123 --> 36:16.394
(grunting)

36:23.341 --> 36:27.215
Oh... Oh...

36:29.053 --> 36:31.357
(groaning)

36:33.227 --> 36:36.300
My buddy can't
handle his liquor.

36:36.367 --> 36:37.335
Come on, buddy.

36:37.402 --> 36:38.839
Let's get you home.

36:38.906 --> 36:41.277
Get you to bed,
where you can sleep peacefully.

36:41.343 --> 36:44.283
-(door opens)
-(entry bells jingle)

36:46.220 --> 36:47.890
(car door opens)

36:49.861 --> 36:51.498
(car door closes)

37:00.315 --> 37:02.285
(engine starts)

37:02.352 --> 37:04.223
(car departs)

37:27.870 --> 37:29.941
(engine stops)

37:48.946 --> 37:50.983
-PATRICK: Hello?
-Patrick, the killer has Henry.

37:51.050 --> 37:52.753
Wh-What? Gino...

37:52.820 --> 37:54.389
I need you.

